 Opposition steps up pressure
A STAFF REPORTERCalcutta: Former CAB assistant secretary Biswarup Dey has demanded that president Prasun Mukherjee step down from his post considering the recent developments. After he was transferred by the state government in regard to the Rizwanur Rahman case, he should step down on his own, Dey said on Thursday. The current opposition member will shoot off a letter to Mukherjee on Monday demanding his resignation. Though a section of the affiliated units  who stood by the former police commissioner during the last CAB elections  are in dilemma regarding the step-down issue, the ruling group appears unperturbed. Mukherjees transfer has nothing to do with the CAB since it is an autonomous body, one of his close associates said. 
